The decision to place him alongside Yuki Tsunoda at RB has generated excitement and speculation, raising questions about Hadjar's ability to compete at the F1 level. Despite being a rookie, Hadjar's impressive performances and strong drive make him a promising addition to the RB squad.

name: Crypto news
summary: Cryptocurrency news this week has been dominated by price fluctuations and security concerns. North Korea is reportedly behind a $1.3 billion cryptocurrency theft, while Bitcoin has surged past $107,000 on hopes for a US strategic reserve. Other tokens like XRP, Ethereum, and Solana have seen declines due to a hawkish Fed. Amidst the market volatility, analysts are questioning the severity of the ongoing crypto bloodbath. Despite the fluctuations, Bitcoin has set a new record above $107,000, leading to speculation about luxury brands accepting crypto payments. However, Bitcoin's price has since fallen more than 10%. Despite the recent downtrend, traders have been taking profits in XRP, AVAX, and Solana, while Bitcoin remains above $104,000. The Giving Block has released a list of the 2024 Crypto Impact 100, highlighting organizations using crypto for positive impact, suggesting that cryptocurrency has potential to become more mainstream if it addresses its challenges.

name: Keith Pitt
summary: Several key members of the Australian Coalition government, including Nationals MP Keith Pitt, have announced their resignations. Pitt criticized the Coalition's approach to climate change, citing concerns about emissions targets. His departure, along with the exits of other MPs, has prompted Liberal Party leader Peter Dutton to announce plans to revamp his frontbench team ahead of the upcoming election. Meanwhile, Nationals senator Matt Canavan suggested that the government's introduction of nuclear power was a political ploy, while Labor's Simon Birmingham downplayed any tensions within the Coalition. Pitt's resignation has sparked discussions about the future of the Nationals party, with some suggesting that his exit could weaken the party's support in rural areas.

name: Strikers
summary: Strikes across various sectors have made recent headlines. Canada Post workers, frustrated by the negotiation process, picketed until the last moment before returning to work. In Thunder Bay, postal strikers face uncertainty after being ordered back to work. The Alberta Federation of Labour condemned the federal government's actions against CUPW strikers, alleging it undermined collective bargaining. In sports, Monaco seeks to fill a void in their offense following an injury to a striker, with Kolo Muani emerging as a potential solution. The Big Bash League saw victories for the Adelaide Strikers, with Short and Pope contributing to their first win of the season. Hunger strikers expressed disappointment after legislative efforts to secure driver's licenses for undocumented immigrants failed in Michigan. In cricket, Dottin led the Adelaide Strikers to their maiden WBBL title. Notably, EA Sports FC 25 highlighted the top meta strikers, including Aaron Jones who joined the Sylhet Strikers for the 2025 Bangladesh Premier League.
